Should look something like this.

```python
class LinkableContract(Contract):
    ...
    # this is what allows this value to be set with `kwargs` in the `factory` method
    needs_bytecode_linking = None

    @classmethod
    def factory(cls, web3, class_name=None, **kwargs):
        needs_bytecode_linking = ...  # whatever check needs to be done to figure this out
        kwargs = assoc(kwargs, 'needs_bytecode_linking', needs_bytecode_linking)
        return super(LinkableContract, cls).factory(web3, class_name, **kwargs)
```

The main `factory` method uses `PropertyCheckingFactory` which is a metaclass which injects all of the given `kwargs` as class properties, but **only if** the class or one of the base classes already has the property (to restrict accidental injection of new class properties due to typos, etc).

